                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="132287" author="olivergierke" created="Wed, 21 Sep 2016 12:03:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am assuming you&apos;re talking about a controller method here? Who&apos;s resolving the &lt;tt&gt;Pageable&lt;/tt&gt; in the first place? What does the request look like? What does your setup for &lt;tt&gt;PageableHandlerMethodArgumentResolver&lt;/tt&gt;} look like?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="132289" author="igler" created="Wed, 21 Sep 2016 13:25:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, a controller method. The request is &quot;http://localhost:8080/api/languages/9dbf1bf3-3b52-4b88-a356-2f9b6edece04/translations&quot;. I have no manual setup for &quot;PageableHandlerMethodArgumentResolver&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="132303" author="igler" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 07:40:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If I replace @RepositoryRestController through @Controller, then Pageable is initialized with default values (if not set through url-parameters).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="132307" author="olivergierke" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2016 08:56:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like the newly introduced &lt;tt&gt;MappingAwarePageableArgumentResolver&lt;/tt&gt; (to fix &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAREST-883&quot; title=&quot;Sort mapping does not consider Jackson customizations in field names&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATAREST-883&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATAREST-883&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) accidentally drops &lt;tt&gt;Pageable&lt;/tt&gt; instances that don&apos;t have no &lt;tt&gt;Sort&lt;/tt&gt; instance attached to it, which unfortunately is the case for the default one being returned from &lt;tt&gt;PageableHandlerMethodArgumentResolver&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="132359" author="otrosien" created="Fri, 23 Sep 2016 07:06:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;.. got bitten by that, too. Is there a known work-around?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="132360" author="olivergierke" created="Fri, 23 Sep 2016 08:15:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So far, it looks like the only way is manually checking the instance for &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; and manually assigning the default then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="132365" author="mp911de" created="Fri, 23 Sep 2016 09:25:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another workaround is using &lt;tt&gt;DefaultedPageable&lt;/tt&gt; that contains the resolved &lt;tt&gt;Pageable&lt;/tt&gt; (Our repository controllers use primarily &lt;tt&gt;DefaultedPageable&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="132390" author="olivergierke" created="Fri, 23 Sep 2016 13:33:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix is in place and snapshots should be available soon. Would be cool if you could give them a spin.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="132573" author="igler" created="Wed, 5 Oct 2016 13:27:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;DefaultedPageable and Hopper-SR4 both fix the problem. Thanx.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
